        <h1>LeetCode 796: Rotate String (C++)</h1>
        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                Given two strings str and target, check if target is a rotation of str. A rotation of a string is
                created by taking some characters from the beginning and appending them to the end. For example, "abcd"
                rotated by 2 positions becomes "cdab".
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: str = "abcd", target = "cdab"<br>
                Output: true<br>
                Explanation: "cdab" is a rotation of "abcd" (rotated 2 positions to the left).
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    bool rotateString(string str, string target) {
        if (str.length() != target.length()) return false;
        string combined = str + str; // simulate all rotations
        return combined.find(target) != string::npos; 
    }
};</code></pre>
